OL,6,FOther senior party figures are anxious
OL,7,Fabout the size of a rebellion, saying
OL,8,F"it is a problem", "we are talking
OL,9,Flarge numbers", and "(the government)
OL,10,Fneed to bring something forward".
OL,12,FIn a sign Downing Street are
OL,13,Fconcerned, government whips have made
OL,14,Fthe unusual move of already indicating
OL,15,Fto potential rebels that they can be
OL,16,Fabsent for the vote and therefore
OL,17,Fabstain.
OL,19,FWhy are there so many different
OL,20,Fnumbers flying around?
