OL,4,Ccuts as Labour revolt grows
OL,6,FAs rebelling MPs scramble to gather
OL,7,Fsupport and Downing Street strive to
OL,8,Fmake sure the plans are voted through,
OL,9,Feveryone is trying to put a number on
OL,10,Fexactly how many MPs could vote
OL,11,Fagainst the government.
OL,13,FITV News has that number at 49 -
OL,14,Fincluding 42 who publicly signed a
OL,15,Fletter against the cuts, and an
OL,16,Fadditional seven who have privately
OL,17,Fsaid they can't back the plans.
