OL,3,CAlmost 50 MPs to rebel over welfare
OL,4,Ccuts as Labour revolt grows
OL,6,FWhile 42 MPs have come out publicly,
OL,7,Fmore than 80 MPs are understood to
OL,8,Fhave signed a private letter urging
OL,9,Fthe government to delay the changes
OL,10,Fand rethink. ITV News understands
OL,11,Fthere are at least six MPs who have
OL,12,Fsigned both letters.
OL,14,FBut many Labour backbenchers believe a
OL,15,Flarge chunk of the 80 people who have
OL,16,Fsigned the private letter won't
OL,17,Factually vote against the plans, and
OL,18,Fare instead likely to abstain or
OL,19,Fultimately vote with the government.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/15
