OL,6,FWhen pressed on whether she might
OL,7,Fchange course in light of the growing
OL,8,Frebellion, Work and Pensions Secretary
OL,9,FLiz Kendall stood by the radical
OL,10,Fchanges.
OL,12,F"We are absolutely right to say it is
OL,13,Fnot good enough that 2.8 million
OL,14,Fpeople have been written off out of
OL,15,Fthe work place due to long term
OL,16,Fsickness, a million young people not
OL,17,Fin education, employment or training.
OL,19,F"We have to make sure those people
OL,20,Fhave the chances and choices they
OL,21,Fdeserve to work".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/15
